1
00:00:09,120 --> 00:00:10,120
(LIQUID DRIPPING)

2
00:00:19,400 --> 00:00:20,600
BUZZER: Lights.

3
00:00:41,920 --> 00:00:43,600
(CODE BEEPING, DOOR BUZZING)

4
00:00:46,360 --> 00:00:47,560
JIMMY: Lights.

5
00:00:48,880 --> 00:00:52,000
You know the drill, people.
Acid visors down and locked.

6
00:00:52,080 --> 00:00:53,280
Buzzer.

7
00:01:05,240 --> 00:01:09,800
-Reading of 9.7.
-JIMMY: Sounds a bit low for Unrefined.

8
00:01:09,880 --> 00:01:12,440
JIMMY: How's the average?
JENNIFER: The acid potency stats

9
00:01:12,520 --> 00:01:15,600
have definitely dropped below the mean
during the last quarter.

10
00:01:15,680 --> 00:01:18,440
-Prettier than a computer, isn't she?
-Give over, Buzz.

11
00:01:18,520 --> 00:01:19,560
Whoa!

12
00:01:20,720 --> 00:01:23,600
Buzzer! Buzz!

13
00:01:26,720 --> 00:01:31,760
Oh, great. Nice going, twinkle-toes.

14
00:01:31,840 --> 00:01:34,600
I shouldn't have swung at him.
Sorry, Buzz. My bad.

15
00:01:34,680 --> 00:01:36,840
No, you're all right. Jimmy?

16
00:01:37,640 --> 00:01:39,800
Well, no point
carrying you back legless.

17
00:01:39,880 --> 00:01:41,560
Sorry, Buzzer, you're dead.

18
00:01:41,640 --> 00:01:45,280
Oh, this is a right pain in the arm our.
Heart's gone now.

19
00:01:46,280 --> 00:01:48,960
Look, we'd best get off.
Got to write this one up for the boss.

20
00:01:49,040 --> 00:01:52,000
-Those suits cost a bomb.
-(BUZZ GRUNTING)

21
00:01:52,080 --> 00:01:55,320
If I miss my boy's birthday
filling out forms, I'll kill you again.

22
00:01:58,040 --> 00:01:59,800
Lights.

23
00:01:59,880 --> 00:02:01,480
JENNIFER: I'm looking at these readings,
Jimmy,

24
00:02:01,560 --> 00:02:03,480
and the potency stats are way too low.

25
00:02:03,560 --> 00:02:07,280
We may have to take that read again.
This thing is still jamming up on me.

26
00:02:07,360 --> 00:02:10,600
So, uh, I think we'd better talk about
what just happened back there.

27
00:02:13,400 --> 00:02:15,800
I could get compensation.
I've seen the holo-ads.

28
00:02:15,880 --> 00:02:18,600
"Had an accident in the workplace?”
Yeah, I have, as it goes.

29
00:02:18,680 --> 00:02:20,480
-I've melted.
-Let it go.

30
00:02:20,560 --> 00:02:23,600
Look, just remember, when you're doing
your report, it wasn't my fault.

31
00:02:23,680 --> 00:02:24,680
She took a swing at me.

32
00:02:24,760 --> 00:02:27,240
I never touched you.
You've got two left feet, Buzzer.

33
00:02:27,320 --> 00:02:29,000
I haven't got two left feet.

34
00:02:29,080 --> 00:02:33,560
Or any arms, neck, head, the chin.
This body costs money, love.

35
00:02:33,640 --> 00:02:35,480
Not as much as that acid suit.

36
00:02:36,520 --> 00:02:39,120
Oh, lighten up.
It's not like anyone was hurt.

37
00:02:39,680 --> 00:02:40,680
(ACID HISSING)

38
00:02:44,280 --> 00:02:46,440
(DOCTOR WHO THEME)

39
00:03:35,360 --> 00:03:36,600
Forty-six.

40
00:03:36,680 --> 00:03:37,840
Rubbishy, rubbishy rubbish.

41
00:03:37,920 --> 00:03:41,680
-Hello! It's a double-top.
-Wrong side of the wire, mister.

42
00:03:42,040 --> 00:03:46,400
-You're on the oche, Red.
-I'm not. Stop trying to put me off.

43
00:03:54,400 --> 00:03:56,720
Who wants fish and chips?

44
00:03:56,800 --> 00:03:59,560
I'll drop you both off.
Take your time. Don't rush.

45
00:03:59,640 --> 00:04:02,040
-Er...and you?
-Uh, things to do.

46
00:04:02,120 --> 00:04:03,760
Things involving other things.

47
00:04:03,840 --> 00:04:06,240
Well, we'll stay with you.
We'll do the other things.

48
00:04:06,480 --> 00:04:07,800
Nope.

49
00:04:07,880 --> 00:04:11,720
Whatever you're up to,
I'd personally like to be a part of it.

50
00:04:14,000 --> 00:04:15,120
What?

51
00:04:16,800 --> 00:04:18,280
(ALARM SOUNDING)

52
00:04:20,480 --> 00:04:22,080
-(AMY SCREAMS)
-Whoa!

53
00:04:23,680 --> 00:04:25,920
Solar tsunami.
Came directly from your sun.

54
00:04:26,000 --> 00:04:28,760
A tidal wave of radiation.
Big, big, big!

55
00:04:34,080 --> 00:04:37,880
-Uh, Doctor, my tummy's going funny.
-Well, the gyrator disconnected.

56
00:04:37,960 --> 00:04:39,880
Target tracking is out.

57
00:04:42,880 --> 00:04:45,200
(DOCTOR GRUNTING, AMY YELLING)

58
00:04:50,920 --> 00:04:52,840
Assume the position!

59
00:04:52,920 --> 00:04:54,240
(SCREAMS)

60
00:04:57,400 --> 00:04:58,800
(SCREAMS)

61
00:05:00,680 --> 00:05:02,000
(PANTING)

62
00:05:03,040 --> 00:05:04,360
(PANTING)

63
00:05:07,520 --> 00:05:08,880
Textbook landing.

64
00:05:08,960 --> 00:05:11,760
Behold! A cockerel!

65
00:05:12,560 --> 00:05:14,160
Love a cockerel.

66
00:05:15,920 --> 00:05:20,000
And underneath, a monastery,
uh, 13th century.

67
00:05:20,080 --> 00:05:22,240
Oh, we've gone all medieval.

68
00:05:22,320 --> 00:05:25,680
-I'm not sure about that.
-Really? Medieval expert, are you?

69
00:05:25,760 --> 00:05:28,440
No, it's just that
I can hear Dusty Springfield.

70
00:05:28,520 --> 00:05:34,480
# You don't have to say you love me
Just be close at hand

71
00:05:34,920 --> 00:05:36,280
# You don't have to... #

72
00:05:36,360 --> 00:05:37,840
These fissures are new.

73
00:05:37,920 --> 00:05:40,520
Solar tsunami sent out
a huge wave of gamma particles.

74
00:05:40,600 --> 00:05:44,160
This is caused by a magnetic quake
that occurs just before the wave hits.

75
00:05:44,240 --> 00:05:48,040
-Well, the monastery's standing.
-Yeah, for now.

76
00:05:48,120 --> 00:05:52,040
-Doctor, look.
-Yeah. It's a supply pipe.

77
00:05:53,440 --> 00:05:57,520
Ceramic inner lining.
Something corrosive.

78
00:05:59,040 --> 00:06:02,400
They're pumping something nasty
off this island to the mainland.

79
00:06:02,480 --> 00:06:05,720
My mum's a massive fan
of Dusty Springfield.

80
00:06:05,800 --> 00:06:07,720
Who isn't?

81
00:06:07,800 --> 00:06:11,600
Right, let's go!
Satisfy our rabid curiosity.

82
00:06:11,680 --> 00:06:14,840
# ...loneliness

83
00:06:15,240 --> 00:06:19,800
# There's nothing left to feel

84
00:06:19,880 --> 00:06:21,760
# You don't have to say... #

85
00:06:21,840 --> 00:06:24,480
So, where are these
Dusty Springfield-loving monks, then?

86
00:06:24,560 --> 00:06:26,600
I think we're here. This is it.

87
00:06:26,680 --> 00:06:28,800
Doctor, what are you talking about?
We've never been here before.

88
00:06:28,880 --> 00:06:31,680
-We came here by accident.
-Hmm? Accident?

89
00:06:31,920 --> 00:06:34,120
-Yes, I know. Accident.
-Ah! Ow!

90
00:06:34,200 --> 00:06:36,000
Acid. They're pumping acid
off this island.

91
00:06:36,080 --> 00:06:38,320
That's old stuff.
Fresh acid, you wouldn't have a finger.

92
00:06:39,440 --> 00:06:40,440
Hmm.

93
00:06:40,520 --> 00:06:43,360
GUARD: Intruder alert! Intruder alert!

94
00:06:43,440 --> 00:06:45,400
There are people coming. Well, almost.

95
00:06:45,480 --> 00:06:47,160
-Almost coming?
-Almost people.

96
00:06:48,280 --> 00:06:50,360
-I think we should really be going.
-AMY: Come on!

97
00:06:50,440 --> 00:06:52,320
I am telling you,
when something runs toward you,

98
00:06:52,400 --> 00:06:54,120
it's never for a nice reason. (GRUNTS)

99
00:07:03,320 --> 00:07:06,320
-What are all these harnesses for?
-Uh, the "almost people"?

100
00:07:06,400 --> 00:07:08,600
What are they, prisoners?
Or are they meditating, or what?

101
00:07:08,680 --> 00:07:11,760
Well, at the moment
they fall into the "or what" category.

102
00:07:11,840 --> 00:07:14,640
GUARD: Halt and remain calm.

103
00:07:14,720 --> 00:07:16,640
Well, we've halted.
How are we all doing on the calm front?

104
00:07:16,720 --> 00:07:18,920
Don't move!

105
00:07:22,920 --> 00:07:25,800
Stay back, Jen.
We don't know who they are.

106
00:07:25,880 --> 00:07:28,480
So let's ask them. Who the hell are you?

107
00:07:28,560 --> 00:07:30,160
Well, I'm The Doctor
and this is Amy and Rory

108
00:07:30,240 --> 00:07:31,400
and it's all very nice, isn't it?

109
00:07:31,480 --> 00:07:34,520
Hold up. You're all...
What are you all, like identical twins?

110
00:07:35,840 --> 00:07:38,160
This is an Alpha-grade
industrial facility.

111
00:07:38,240 --> 00:07:39,560
Unless you work for the military

112
00:07:39,640 --> 00:07:42,800
or for Morpeth Jetsan,
you are in big trouble.

113
00:07:43,720 --> 00:07:47,040
Actually, you're in big trouble.

114
00:07:47,120 --> 00:07:49,880
Meteorological Department? Since when?

115
00:07:49,960 --> 00:07:52,760
-Since you were hit by a solar wave.
-Which we survived.

116
00:07:52,840 --> 00:07:55,560
Just, by the look of it.
And there's a bigger one on the way.

117
00:07:55,640 --> 00:07:57,640
Which we'll also survive.

118
00:07:57,720 --> 00:07:59,360
Dicken, scan for bugs.

119
00:07:59,440 --> 00:08:01,600
Backs against the wall. Now.

120
00:08:02,320 --> 00:08:04,480
You're not a monastery,
you're a factory.

121
00:08:04,560 --> 00:08:06,520
22nd century Army-owned factory.

122
00:08:06,600 --> 00:08:07,640
You're Army?

123
00:08:07,720 --> 00:08:10,880
No, love, we're contractors.
And you're trespassers.

124
00:08:13,960 --> 00:08:15,600
It's clear, boss.

125
00:08:16,320 --> 00:08:18,520
All right, weatherman,
your ID checks out.

126
00:08:18,600 --> 00:08:21,320
If there's another solar storm,
what are you going to do about it?

127
00:08:21,400 --> 00:08:22,560
Hand out sunblock?

128
00:08:22,640 --> 00:08:23,680
(LAUGHS)

129
00:08:23,760 --> 00:08:26,360
I need to see your critical systems.

130
00:08:26,440 --> 00:08:27,760
Which one?

131
00:08:29,520 --> 00:08:31,240
You know which one.

132
00:08:38,080 --> 00:08:39,400
(BUBBLING)

133
00:09:01,800 --> 00:09:03,040
And there you are.

134
00:09:03,120 --> 00:09:06,880
Meet the government's
worst kept secret. The Flesh.

135
00:09:07,440 --> 00:09:09,480
It's fully programmable matter.

136
00:09:09,560 --> 00:09:11,720
In fact, it's even learning
to replicate itself

137
00:09:11,800 --> 00:09:13,040
at the cellular level.

138
00:09:13,120 --> 00:09:16,160
Right. Brilliant. Lost.

139
00:09:16,240 --> 00:09:17,360
Okay.

140
00:09:18,360 --> 00:09:19,560
Once a reading's been taken,

141
00:09:19,640 --> 00:09:22,480
we can manipulate
its molecular structure into anything,

142
00:09:22,560 --> 00:09:26,760
replicate a living organism down
to the hairs on its chinny chin chin.

143
00:09:26,840 --> 00:09:29,440
Even clothes.
And everything's identical.

144
00:09:29,520 --> 00:09:32,040
-Eyes, voice...
-Mind, soul.

145
00:09:32,120 --> 00:09:33,720
Don't be fooled, Doctor,

146
00:09:33,800 --> 00:09:37,040
it acts like life but it still needs
to be controlled by us,

147
00:09:37,120 --> 00:09:38,840
from those harnesses you saw.

148
00:09:38,920 --> 00:09:44,440
Wait, whoa, hold it.
So, you're Flesh now?

149
00:09:44,520 --> 00:09:46,760
I'm lying in a harness
back in that chamber.

150
00:09:47,320 --> 00:09:49,080
We all are, except Jennifer here.

151
00:09:49,160 --> 00:09:52,920
Don't be scared. This thing,
just like operating a forklift truck.

152
00:09:53,000 --> 00:09:55,240
You said it could grow.
Only living things grow.

153
00:09:55,320 --> 00:09:57,200
Moss grows. It's no more than that.

154
00:09:57,880 --> 00:10:01,280
This acid is so dangerous,
we were losing a worker every week.

155
00:10:02,360 --> 00:10:06,200
So now we mine the acid
using these doppelgangers, or Gangers.

156
00:10:06,280 --> 00:10:08,320
If these bodies get burnt
or fall in the acid...

157
00:10:08,400 --> 00:10:10,320
Then who the hell cares? Right, Jen?

158
00:10:12,000 --> 00:10:17,360
Nerve endings automatically cut off,
like airbags being discharged.

159
00:10:17,440 --> 00:10:19,920
So we wake up and get a new Ganger.

160
00:10:20,880 --> 00:10:23,720
It's weird but you get used to it.

161
00:10:23,800 --> 00:10:26,600
Jennifer, I want you in your Ganger.
Get back to the harness.

162
00:10:29,480 --> 00:10:31,120
-Hang on.
-What's he up to?

163
00:10:31,200 --> 00:10:32,600
What are you up to, pal?

164
00:10:33,400 --> 00:10:35,600
Stop it. Ah...

165
00:10:36,600 --> 00:10:41,120
Strange, it was like for a moment there
it was scanning me.

166
00:10:41,200 --> 00:10:42,560
(BUBBLING)

167
00:10:43,520 --> 00:10:44,720
Doctor.

168
00:10:46,160 --> 00:10:48,560
-Get back, Doctor, leave it alone!
-(GROANING)

169
00:10:53,640 --> 00:10:55,600
(CRIES OUT) I understand.

170
00:10:57,080 --> 00:10:58,240
Doctor?

171
00:10:58,320 --> 00:11:00,560
-Are you all right?
-Incredible.

172
00:11:01,200 --> 00:11:05,000
You have no idea. No idea.

173
00:11:05,360 --> 00:11:08,240
I mean, I felt it in my mind.
I reached out to it and it to me.

174
00:11:08,320 --> 00:11:10,080
Don't fiddle with the money, Doctor.

175
00:11:10,160 --> 00:11:12,160
How can you be so blinkered?
It's alive. So alive.

176
00:11:12,240 --> 00:11:15,520
You're piling your lives,
your personalities directly into it.

177
00:11:17,360 --> 00:11:19,880
(STORM CRASHING)

178
00:11:19,960 --> 00:11:21,680
It's the solar storm.

179
00:11:22,800 --> 00:11:27,080
The first waves come in pairs.
Pre-shock and fore-shock. It's close.

180
00:11:27,160 --> 00:11:28,920
Buzzer, we got anything
from the mainland yet?

181
00:11:29,000 --> 00:11:31,160
No, the comms are still
too jammed with radiation.

182
00:11:31,240 --> 00:11:34,920
Okay, then we'll keep pumping acid
until the mainland says stop.

183
00:11:35,000 --> 00:11:38,360
Now, why don't you stand back
and let us impress you?

184
00:11:41,360 --> 00:11:44,680
COMPUTER: ID confirmed. Jennifer Lucas.

185
00:11:44,760 --> 00:11:46,280
The meter is running.

186
00:12:06,560 --> 00:12:10,040
Cardio and respiratory, online.

187
00:12:10,840 --> 00:12:15,360
Motor functions, online.

188
00:12:16,880 --> 00:12:18,280
Plumbing in.

189
00:12:19,840 --> 00:12:22,200
(MACHINE POWERING UP)

190
00:12:41,200 --> 00:12:42,520
(GROANING)

191
00:12:57,240 --> 00:12:58,800
-(INHALES DEEPLY)
-Oh!

192
00:13:00,240 --> 00:13:01,240
(EXHALES)

193
00:13:04,040 --> 00:13:06,400
Well, I can see
why you keep it in a church.

194
00:13:06,480 --> 00:13:10,280
-Miracle of life.
-No need to get poncy. It's just gunge.

195
00:13:10,360 --> 00:13:12,160
Guys, we need to get to work.

196
00:13:12,240 --> 00:13:14,480
Okay, everybody, let's crack on.

197
00:13:14,560 --> 00:13:17,920
-(STORM CRASHING)
-DOCTOR: Did I mention the solar storm?

198
00:13:18,000 --> 00:13:20,480
-You need to get out of here.
-Where do you want us to go?

199
00:13:20,560 --> 00:13:21,720
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

200
00:13:21,800 --> 00:13:24,080
-We're on a tiny island.
-Well, I can get you all off it.

201
00:13:24,160 --> 00:13:26,320
CLEAVES: Don't be ridiculous.
We've got a job to do.

202
00:13:26,400 --> 00:13:27,880
It's coming.

203
00:13:27,960 --> 00:13:30,040
That's the alarm.

204
00:13:30,120 --> 00:13:33,320
-How do you get power?
-We're solar. We use a solar router.

205
00:13:33,400 --> 00:13:34,880
-The weathervane.
-Big problem.

206
00:13:34,960 --> 00:13:38,480
Boss, maybe if the storm's back,
we should get underground.

207
00:13:38,840 --> 00:13:40,120
The factory's seen better days.

208
00:13:40,200 --> 00:13:42,320
The acid pipes might not withstand
another hit.

209
00:13:42,400 --> 00:13:44,120
We have 200 tons of acid to pump out.

210
00:13:44,200 --> 00:13:46,040
We fall behind,
we stay another rotation.

211
00:13:46,120 --> 00:13:48,320
-Anyone want that?
-Please.

212
00:13:48,400 --> 00:13:50,080
You're making a massive mistake here.

213
00:13:50,160 --> 00:13:52,080
You're right at the crossroads of it.
Don't turn the wrong way.

214
00:13:52,160 --> 00:13:55,200
If you don't, if you don't
prepare for this storm,

215
00:13:55,280 --> 00:13:57,000
you are all in terrible danger.

216
00:13:57,080 --> 00:13:58,680
Understand?

217
00:13:58,760 --> 00:14:01,960
My factory, my rules.

218
00:14:06,480 --> 00:14:07,920
I need to check
the progress of the storm.

219
00:14:08,000 --> 00:14:09,640
Monitoring station.

220
00:14:09,720 --> 00:14:12,200
-Mmm.
-Monitoring station.

221
00:14:12,280 --> 00:14:14,480
Three lefts, a right, and a left.
Third door on your left.

222
00:14:14,560 --> 00:14:15,560
Thank you.

223
00:14:20,120 --> 00:14:22,920
(ALARM SOUNDING, THUNDER CRASHING)

224
00:14:24,760 --> 00:14:27,280
(GRUNTS) Waves disturbing
the Earth's magnetic field.

225
00:14:27,360 --> 00:14:30,080
There is going to be the mother
and father of all power surges.

226
00:14:30,160 --> 00:14:31,840
See this weathervane,
the cock-a-doodle-do?

227
00:14:31,920 --> 00:14:34,120
It's a solar router feeding
the whole factory with solar power.

228
00:14:34,200 --> 00:14:36,600
When that wave hits, kaboom!

229
00:14:37,400 --> 00:14:40,200
I've got to get to that cockerel
before all hell breaks loose.

230
00:14:41,680 --> 00:14:43,440
I never thought
I'd get to say that again.

231
00:14:43,520 --> 00:14:46,360
(SIGHS) Amy, breathe.

232
00:14:47,280 --> 00:14:49,840
Yeah. I mean, thanks, I'll try.

233
00:14:53,120 --> 00:14:55,040
(THUNDER CLAPPING)

234
00:15:06,480 --> 00:15:08,280
(ELECTRICITY SURGING)

235
00:15:26,720 --> 00:15:28,200
(ACID HISSING)

236
00:15:36,360 --> 00:15:38,280
(GRUNTING)

237
00:15:41,320 --> 00:15:42,320
Er...

238
00:15:48,440 --> 00:15:49,440
(SCREAMING)

239
00:15:51,280 --> 00:15:52,600
Ow!

240
00:15:54,440 --> 00:15:56,200
(SCREAMING)

241
00:15:57,840 --> 00:15:59,520
(SCREAMING)

242
00:16:14,640 --> 00:16:15,640
(GRUNTS)

243
00:16:16,800 --> 00:16:18,280
(INHALES DEEPLY)

244
00:16:34,520 --> 00:16:39,880
Oh! For want of a better word, "Ow"!

245
00:16:41,480 --> 00:16:44,400
Cleaves! You're not in your harness.

246
00:16:44,480 --> 00:16:48,160
-I'm sorry, Doctor. You were right.
-You've lost all power to the factory.

247
00:16:48,240 --> 00:16:52,040
-Doctor, I abandoned my team.
-Then let's go get them.

248
00:16:53,240 --> 00:16:55,480
How long would you say
we were unconscious for, Cleaves?

249
00:16:55,560 --> 00:16:56,800
Not long. A minute, two minutes?

250
00:16:56,880 --> 00:16:58,480
I'd hazard we've been out
a teensy bit longer.

251
00:16:58,560 --> 00:17:00,080
-Well, how long?
-An hour.

252
00:17:00,160 --> 00:17:03,080
I've seen whole worlds turned inside-out
in an hour.

253
00:17:03,160 --> 00:17:05,400
A lot can go wrong in an hour.

254
00:17:06,520 --> 00:17:07,560
(SIGHS)

255
00:17:08,200 --> 00:17:09,240
(GRUNTING)

256
00:17:11,400 --> 00:17:13,400
I feel like I've been toasted.

257
00:17:13,480 --> 00:17:15,840
-What the hell happened?
-The tsunami happened. You hurt?

258
00:17:15,920 --> 00:17:18,840
It feels like the National Grid's run
through my bones, but apart from that...

259
00:17:18,920 --> 00:17:20,840
I hope the meter's not bust.
I still want to get paid.

260
00:17:20,920 --> 00:17:22,720
-Why...
-Jennifer!

261
00:17:23,240 --> 00:17:27,440
-(WHIMPERING)
-Jennifer? Hey, all right.

262
00:17:29,040 --> 00:17:32,800
-It hurt so much.
-Hey, it's okay. It's over.

263
00:17:33,680 --> 00:17:35,880
-I couldn't get out of my harness.
-Shh, shh, shh.

264
00:17:35,960 --> 00:17:38,160
I thought I was going to die.

265
00:17:38,880 --> 00:17:40,640
Welcome to my world.

266
00:17:46,960 --> 00:17:49,960
Doctor, these are all real people,
so where are their Gangers?

267
00:17:50,040 --> 00:17:52,800
Don't worry. When the link shuts down,
the Gangers return to pure Flesh.

268
00:17:52,880 --> 00:17:54,640
Now, the storm's left us
with acid leaks all over

269
00:17:54,720 --> 00:17:55,840
so we need to contact the mainland.

270
00:17:55,920 --> 00:17:57,360
They can have a rescue shuttle
out here in no time.

271
00:17:57,440 --> 00:18:00,280
(YOU DON'T HAVE TO SAY YOU LOVE ME
PLAYING)

272
00:18:03,080 --> 00:18:06,000
That's my record.
Who's playing my record?

273
00:18:06,080 --> 00:18:09,760
-Your Gangers, they've gone walkabout.
-No, it's impossible.

274
00:18:09,840 --> 00:18:11,520
They're not active.
Cars don't fly themselves,

275
00:18:11,600 --> 00:18:14,040
cranes don't lift themselves
and Gangers don't...

276
00:18:14,120 --> 00:18:20,080
# When I said I needed you... #

277
00:18:29,800 --> 00:18:32,200
-No way.
-I don't...

278
00:18:32,280 --> 00:18:34,160
I... I don't believe this.

279
00:18:34,240 --> 00:18:37,080
They could've escaped
through the service door at the back.

280
00:18:39,720 --> 00:18:41,920
This is just like the Isle of Sheppey.

281
00:18:44,040 --> 00:18:47,400
It would seem the storm
has animated your Gangers.

282
00:18:47,480 --> 00:18:49,200
They've ransacked everything.

283
00:18:49,280 --> 00:18:53,160
-Not ransacked. Searched.
-Through our stuff!

284
00:18:53,240 --> 00:18:54,440
Their stuff.

285
00:18:54,520 --> 00:18:56,120
-Searching for what?
-Confirmation.

286
00:18:56,200 --> 00:18:57,800
They need to know
their memories are real.

287
00:18:57,880 --> 00:18:59,480
Oh, so they've got flaming memories now?

288
00:18:59,560 --> 00:19:01,600
They feel compelled
to connect to their lives.

289
00:19:01,680 --> 00:19:05,120
-Their stolen lives.
-No. Bequeathed. You gave them this.

290
00:19:05,200 --> 00:19:07,760
You poured in your personalities,
emotions, traits, memories,

291
00:19:07,840 --> 00:19:09,480
secrets, everything.
You gave them your lives.

292
00:19:09,560 --> 00:19:12,320
Human lives are amazing.

293
00:19:13,360 --> 00:19:15,600
Are you surprised
they walked off with them?

294
00:19:15,680 --> 00:19:18,160
I'll say it again, Isle of Sheppey.

295
00:19:18,240 --> 00:19:21,120
Ganger got an electric shock,
toddled off, killed his operator

296
00:19:21,200 --> 00:19:23,120
right there in his harness.
I've seen the photos.

297
00:19:23,200 --> 00:19:26,560
-This bloke's ear was all hanging...
-Even if this has actually happened,

298
00:19:26,640 --> 00:19:29,920
they can't remain stable
without us plumbed in to them.

299
00:19:30,360 --> 00:19:31,880
Can they, boss?

300
00:19:36,800 --> 00:19:37,880
Guess we'll find out.

301
00:19:37,960 --> 00:19:40,280
-(GASPS)
-Are you okay?

302
00:19:40,360 --> 00:19:43,960
-Do you need some water?
- I feel funny.

303
00:19:44,040 --> 00:19:45,800
I need the washroom.

304
00:19:46,600 --> 00:19:48,440
I'll come with you.

305
00:19:48,520 --> 00:19:50,720
-(SNEEZES) Sorry.
-Oh. That's okay.

306
00:19:51,520 --> 00:19:55,800
That's me. It's good to have a hobby.
So what?

307
00:19:56,720 --> 00:19:58,480
My Ganger did that all on its own?

308
00:19:58,560 --> 00:20:00,280
Who taught you to do this?

309
00:20:00,960 --> 00:20:01,960
My granddad.

310
00:20:02,040 --> 00:20:04,760
Well, your Ganger's granddad
taught him to do it, too.

311
00:20:05,000 --> 00:20:09,320
You both have the same childhood
memories, just as clear, just as real.

312
00:20:13,120 --> 00:20:15,480
-No.
-Scared, disorientated,

313
00:20:15,560 --> 00:20:20,360
struggling to come to terms
with an entire life in their heads.

314
00:20:23,520 --> 00:20:26,840
The Doctor's always saying,
"Don't wander off."

315
00:20:26,920 --> 00:20:30,160
First rule with him, actually,
don't wander off.

316
00:20:30,240 --> 00:20:31,720
I just need a minute.

317
00:20:32,440 --> 00:20:35,520
Oh, yeah. Sure.
Take all the time you need.

318
00:20:37,200 --> 00:20:40,120
I've got your back. You're fine.

319
00:20:46,120 --> 00:20:47,120
(GASPS)

320
00:20:48,480 --> 00:20:51,440
Uh, Jennifer?

321
00:20:52,160 --> 00:20:53,560
(GASPING)

322
00:20:56,080 --> 00:20:59,240
-What, what's up, Jennifer?
-(DOOR CLOSING)

323
00:21:00,840 --> 00:21:02,280
We, uh,

324
00:21:05,080 --> 00:21:06,400
better get going.

325
00:21:09,360 --> 00:21:11,720
Everything okay in there, Jen?

326
00:21:16,480 --> 00:21:21,120
Just let us live! (GRUNTING)

327
00:21:25,520 --> 00:21:27,360
We need to protect ourselves.

328
00:21:29,640 --> 00:21:33,200
-Are you a violent man, Jimmy?
-No.

329
00:21:33,480 --> 00:21:35,440
Then why would the other Jimmy be?

330
00:21:35,520 --> 00:21:37,920
Tell me you can eat
at a time like this, Doctor.

331
00:21:38,000 --> 00:21:41,080
You told me we were out cold
for a few minutes, Cleaves,

332
00:21:41,160 --> 00:21:43,360
when in fact, it was an hour.

333
00:21:43,760 --> 00:21:45,000
Sorry? I just assumed...

334
00:21:45,080 --> 00:21:47,560
Well, it's not your fault.
Like I said, they're disorientated.

335
00:21:47,640 --> 00:21:50,160
Amy, when you got to the alcoves,
who was in harness?

336
00:21:50,240 --> 00:21:53,000
Um, Jimmy and Dicken
were helping Buzzer out.

337
00:21:53,080 --> 00:21:54,080
Jennifer?

338
00:21:54,160 --> 00:21:56,400
She was standing on her own
when we got to her.

339
00:22:02,640 --> 00:22:05,040
-It's hot.
-(SUCKS BREATH IN) Uh.

340
00:22:07,440 --> 00:22:08,920
Trans-matter's still a little rubbery.

341
00:22:09,000 --> 00:22:11,360
Nerve endings not quite fused properly.

342
00:22:11,440 --> 00:22:14,040
-What are you talking about?
-It's okay.

343
00:22:18,000 --> 00:22:20,200
-Why didn't I feel that?
-You will.

344
00:22:21,000 --> 00:22:22,000
You'll stabilise.

345
00:22:22,080 --> 00:22:24,600
No. Stop it.
You're playing stupid games.

346
00:22:24,680 --> 00:22:25,920
Stop it!

347
00:22:32,080 --> 00:22:38,360
You don't have to hide.
Please, trust me, I'm the Doctor.

348
00:22:41,560 --> 00:22:43,400
Where's the real Cleaves, you thing?

349
00:22:43,480 --> 00:22:45,480
What have you done with her?

350
00:22:45,560 --> 00:22:47,520
That's it. Good, you remember.

351
00:22:47,600 --> 00:22:54,080
This is early Flesh. The early stages
of the technology. So much to learn.

352
00:22:54,160 --> 00:22:56,840
-Doctor, what's happened to her?
-She can't stabilise,

353
00:22:56,920 --> 00:23:00,840
she's shifting between half-formed
and full-formed. For now, at least.

354
00:23:00,920 --> 00:23:02,960
We are living!

355
00:23:04,120 --> 00:23:05,880
(SCREAMING)

356
00:23:10,880 --> 00:23:13,280
-Let her go.
-Doctor, Rory.

357
00:23:13,360 --> 00:23:16,320
-Rory?
-Rory!

358
00:23:16,400 --> 00:23:19,560
Oh, Rory. Rory! Always with the Rory.

359
00:23:19,720 --> 00:23:21,320
(THUNDER CRASHING)

360
00:23:32,400 --> 00:23:34,240
Explosion must've ruptured
the acid feeds.

361
00:23:34,320 --> 00:23:35,520
We're going to need the acid suits.

362
00:23:35,600 --> 00:23:38,800
No, no, no. We haven't got time.
Back, back, back!

363
00:24:01,160 --> 00:24:02,280
JENNIFER: Rory!

364
00:24:07,480 --> 00:24:08,600
Rory?

365
00:24:12,160 --> 00:24:13,320
Rory!

366
00:24:32,960 --> 00:24:33,960
Rory.

367
00:24:34,040 --> 00:24:36,480
Of course, Jennifer's a Ganger, too.

368
00:24:37,680 --> 00:24:39,440
Doctor, you said
they wouldn't be violent.

369
00:24:39,520 --> 00:24:41,200
But I did say
they were scared and angry.

370
00:24:41,280 --> 00:24:45,080
And early technology is what you said.

371
00:24:45,720 --> 00:24:48,560
You seem to know something
about the Flesh.

372
00:24:49,200 --> 00:24:51,760
Do you? Doctor?

373
00:25:00,280 --> 00:25:02,080
You're no weatherman.

374
00:25:02,640 --> 00:25:04,440
Why are you really here?

375
00:25:04,520 --> 00:25:07,200
I have to talk to them. I can fix this.

376
00:25:08,200 --> 00:25:11,360
Wait! What's going on?
Where's the real Jennifer?

377
00:25:12,480 --> 00:25:14,000
(SHUDDERING)

378
00:25:22,480 --> 00:25:25,240
It is too dangerous out here
with acid leaks.

379
00:25:25,320 --> 00:25:26,440
We have to find Rory.

380
00:25:26,520 --> 00:25:28,960
Yes, I'm going back to the Tardis.
Wait for me in the dining hall.

381
00:25:29,040 --> 00:25:31,680
I want us to keep together, okay?
No more wandering off.

382
00:25:31,760 --> 00:25:32,760
And what about Rory?

383
00:25:32,840 --> 00:25:36,360
Well, it would be safer to look
for Rory and Jennifer with the Tardis.

384
00:25:38,040 --> 00:25:39,560
Here we go.

385
00:25:41,920 --> 00:25:43,680
Distress flares.

386
00:25:45,880 --> 00:25:48,480
-Exit?
-Keep going straight. Can't miss it.

387
00:25:48,560 --> 00:25:50,800
But you're never going to get
your vehicle in here.

388
00:25:50,880 --> 00:25:52,600
I'm a great Parker.

389
00:25:55,560 --> 00:25:57,600
Well, we really need those acid suits.

390
00:25:57,680 --> 00:25:59,560
I've sent Buzzer and Dicken to get them.

391
00:25:59,640 --> 00:26:03,960
Fine and dandy. I'm just going to
find my husband. So, cheers.

392
00:26:04,040 --> 00:26:06,800
-Amy, I wouldn't.
-Nor would I.

393
00:26:06,880 --> 00:26:08,640
What can you do, eh?

394
00:26:10,360 --> 00:26:12,640
At least wait for an acid suit!

395
00:26:47,400 --> 00:26:49,400
When I was a little girl,

396
00:26:50,520 --> 00:26:54,240
I got lost on the moors,
wandered off from the picnic.

397
00:26:57,400 --> 00:27:02,240
I can still feel how sore my toes
got inside my red welly boots.

398
00:27:04,440 --> 00:27:09,400
And I imagined another little girl,
just like me, in red wellies.

399
00:27:09,480 --> 00:27:11,560
And she was Jennifer, too.

400
00:27:13,200 --> 00:27:15,520
Except she was a strong Jennifer,

401
00:27:17,520 --> 00:27:19,160
a tough Jennifer.

402
00:27:22,640 --> 00:27:24,560
She'd lead me home.

403
00:27:44,880 --> 00:27:46,920
My name is Jennifer Lucas.

404
00:27:48,080 --> 00:27:50,040
I'm not a factory part.

405
00:27:51,360 --> 00:27:53,560
I had toast for my breakfast.

406
00:27:54,760 --> 00:27:58,520
I wrote a letter to my mum.
And then you arrived.

407
00:27:59,600 --> 00:28:01,840
I noticed your eyes right off.

408
00:28:03,760 --> 00:28:05,280
Did you?

409
00:28:05,360 --> 00:28:09,560
Nice eyes. Kind.

410
00:28:13,600 --> 00:28:15,280
Where's the real Jennifer?

411
00:28:16,560 --> 00:28:19,440
I am Jennifer Lucas!

412
00:28:19,520 --> 00:28:23,440
I remember everything
that happened in her entire life.

413
00:28:23,520 --> 00:28:28,080
Every birthday, every childhood illness.

414
00:28:29,360 --> 00:28:33,560
I feel everything she has ever felt
and more.

415
00:28:33,640 --> 00:28:35,720
I'm not a monster!

416
00:28:35,800 --> 00:28:40,840
I am me. Me! Me! Me!

417
00:28:51,320 --> 00:28:53,400
Why did they do this to us?

418
00:28:55,520 --> 00:28:59,480
Help me, Rory. Help me.

419
00:29:01,280 --> 00:29:03,520
Shh, shh.

420
00:29:09,120 --> 00:29:10,440
(BUBBLING)

421
00:29:17,360 --> 00:29:19,120
(BUBBLING INCREASES)

422
00:29:32,960 --> 00:29:34,920
Trust me.

423
00:29:37,960 --> 00:29:41,080
Oh... What are you doing down there?

424
00:29:42,960 --> 00:29:43,960
Ooh.

425
00:29:46,640 --> 00:29:47,680
Ah!

426
00:29:53,200 --> 00:29:56,480
Ah! Oh! Oh! Oh!

427
00:29:56,560 --> 00:29:58,640
Oh! Ah! Ah!

428
00:30:01,680 --> 00:30:02,840
Clear.

429
00:30:08,920 --> 00:30:11,440
Those damn Gangers
got to the acid suits.

430
00:30:11,520 --> 00:30:13,680
There is acid leaking everywhere.

431
00:30:13,760 --> 00:30:16,400
Did you see the boss' eyes
back there in the hall?

432
00:30:16,480 --> 00:30:19,080
I've never seen a Ganger
look at me like that.

433
00:30:19,160 --> 00:30:22,680
I don't know what they are now
but they ain't us.

434
00:30:23,760 --> 00:30:24,800
(SNEEZES LOUDLY)

435
00:30:25,200 --> 00:30:26,880
(CODE BEEPING, DOOR BUZZING)

436
00:30:47,040 --> 00:30:48,680
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

437
00:30:57,360 --> 00:31:00,120
We have the advantage now.

438
00:31:00,200 --> 00:31:01,640
We have the acid suits.

439
00:31:01,720 --> 00:31:05,320
We can move freely, strike at will.

440
00:31:06,360 --> 00:31:10,560
Are you sure you're feeling better?
No more super-elastic punches?

441
00:31:11,520 --> 00:31:14,560
I'm...different now.

442
00:31:14,640 --> 00:31:18,120
-Stronger.
-The Doctor won't hurt you.

443
00:31:18,200 --> 00:31:20,160
He wants to help, Jennifer. Okay?

444
00:31:20,240 --> 00:31:22,160
You used my name.

445
00:31:22,640 --> 00:31:25,400
You used my name. Thank you.

446
00:31:27,800 --> 00:31:31,960
-Amy's a lucky girl.
-Yeah. She is.

447
00:31:32,040 --> 00:31:34,200
(SIGHS)

448
00:31:35,840 --> 00:31:37,360
Let's go.

449
00:31:53,360 --> 00:31:56,080
Rory. Rory?

450
00:32:18,480 --> 00:32:19,880
(GASPS)

451
00:32:22,640 --> 00:32:26,080
-Amy!
-(GASPS) You're okay.

452
00:32:27,480 --> 00:32:28,960
What happened?

453
00:32:31,480 --> 00:32:34,480
-She needs protecting.
-Jen?

454
00:32:34,560 --> 00:32:36,520
No, it's a Ganger.

455
00:32:36,600 --> 00:32:40,360
-Rory, listen...
-No, you listen! Nobody touches her!

456
00:32:44,400 --> 00:32:45,400
(DOOR BUZZING)

457
00:33:09,280 --> 00:33:11,160
Hello.

458
00:33:11,240 --> 00:33:14,200
-How are you all getting on?
-Why don't you tell us?

459
00:33:14,280 --> 00:33:17,160
Well, we have two choices.
The first is to tear each other apart,

460
00:33:17,240 --> 00:33:21,160
not my favourite. The second is
to knuckle down and work together,

461
00:33:21,240 --> 00:33:24,000
try to work out how
best we can help you.

462
00:33:25,960 --> 00:33:29,480
Now, I know it's hard for you
to hold your fully human form.

463
00:33:29,560 --> 00:33:33,320
That's why you keep shifting
between the Flesh stages. But do try.

464
00:33:33,400 --> 00:33:35,640
It'll make the others
less scared of you.

465
00:33:44,760 --> 00:33:47,600
Where's Jen?
What have you done with her?

466
00:33:47,680 --> 00:33:49,840
I haven't seen her, I swear.

467
00:33:50,480 --> 00:33:54,200
But look, I'm her.
I'm just like her. I'm real.

468
00:33:54,280 --> 00:33:55,760
You're a copy.

469
00:33:56,520 --> 00:33:58,280
You're just pretending to be like her.

470
00:33:58,360 --> 00:34:02,440
Rory, we don't really know anything
about them yet.

471
00:34:02,520 --> 00:34:04,080
-Well...
-And...

472
00:34:05,120 --> 00:34:08,600
I know that she's afraid
and she needs our help.

473
00:34:09,240 --> 00:34:10,240
Rory, would you...

474
00:34:10,320 --> 00:34:13,720
Jimmy, Buzzer, come on, you guys.

475
00:34:14,160 --> 00:34:16,000
We've worked together for two years.

476
00:34:16,080 --> 00:34:17,480
I worked with Jennifer Lucas, not you.

477
00:34:17,560 --> 00:34:19,800
Okay, let's not do anything at all

478
00:34:19,880 --> 00:34:22,880
-until the Doctor gets...
-Until the Doctor gets here. Hello.

479
00:34:32,000 --> 00:34:36,680
-This is...
-You're telling me.

480
00:34:36,760 --> 00:34:40,280
All right, Doctor,
you've brought us together, now what?

481
00:34:40,360 --> 00:34:42,720
Before we do anything,
I have one very important question.

482
00:34:42,800 --> 00:34:44,880
Has anybody got
a pair of shoes I could borrow?

483
00:34:44,960 --> 00:34:48,400
Size 10, although I should
warn you, I have very wide feet.

484
00:34:53,440 --> 00:34:57,800
That's it, Doctor, befriend them,
team up with them, why don't you?

485
00:34:57,880 --> 00:35:00,400
Make a football team. How about that?

486
00:35:01,760 --> 00:35:05,520
You're going to have us all
together singing campfire songs.

487
00:35:07,960 --> 00:35:09,680
The Flesh was never merely moss.

488
00:35:09,760 --> 00:35:12,560
These are not copies.
The storm has hardwired them.

489
00:35:12,640 --> 00:35:15,160
They are becoming people.

490
00:35:15,240 --> 00:35:18,360
-With souls?
-Rubbish! (SNEEZES)

491
00:35:18,440 --> 00:35:20,320
Bless you.

492
00:35:20,400 --> 00:35:24,240
DOCTOR: What? We were all jelly once.
Little jelly eggs sitting in goop.

493
00:35:24,320 --> 00:35:26,000
AMY: Yeah, thanks, too much information.

494
00:35:26,080 --> 00:35:28,680
We are not talking about an accident
that needs to be mopped up.

495
00:35:28,760 --> 00:35:32,000
We are talking about sacred life.
Do you understand?

496
00:35:32,800 --> 00:35:36,480
Good. Now, the Tardis is trapped
in an acid pool.

497
00:35:36,560 --> 00:35:37,560
Once I can reach her,

498
00:35:37,680 --> 00:35:41,240
I can get you all off this island,
humans and Gangers. How does that sound?

499
00:35:41,320 --> 00:35:43,320
Can I make it home for Adam's birthday?

500
00:35:43,400 --> 00:35:45,240
What about me?

501
00:35:45,320 --> 00:35:46,840
He's my son, too.

502
00:35:46,920 --> 00:35:50,600
-You? You really think that?
-I feel it.

503
00:35:50,680 --> 00:35:52,480
Oh, so you were there when he was born,
were you?

504
00:35:52,560 --> 00:35:53,720
Yeah.

505
00:35:55,240 --> 00:35:59,040
I drank about eight pints of tea.

506
00:35:59,120 --> 00:36:02,400
Then they told me I had a wee boy
and I just burst out laughing.

507
00:36:02,480 --> 00:36:03,480
(CHUCKLES)

508
00:36:04,840 --> 00:36:06,520
No idea why.

509
00:36:08,360 --> 00:36:09,760
I miss home,

510
00:36:11,280 --> 00:36:12,800
as much as you.

511
00:36:18,160 --> 00:36:20,560
Look, I'm not going to lie to you,
it's a right old mess, this.

512
00:36:20,640 --> 00:36:22,560
But as you might say up north,

513
00:36:22,640 --> 00:36:26,040
"Oh, well, I'll just go
to t'foot of stairs.” (CHUCKLES)

514
00:36:26,120 --> 00:36:29,680
"Ee by by gum."” Or not. Good. Right.

515
00:36:29,760 --> 00:36:32,520
First step is we get everyone together,
then get everyone safe.

516
00:36:32,600 --> 00:36:34,600
Then get everyone out of here.

517
00:36:34,680 --> 00:36:36,840
But we're still missing
Jennifer and Cleaves.

518
00:36:36,920 --> 00:36:38,360
I'll go and look for them.

519
00:36:39,320 --> 00:36:41,760
I'll give you a hand, if you like.

520
00:36:43,720 --> 00:36:46,080
-Cover more ground.
-Yeah.

521
00:36:47,240 --> 00:36:50,680
-Okay. Thanks.
-This circus has gone on long enough!

522
00:36:53,040 --> 00:36:57,080
Oh, great.
You see, that is just so typically me.

523
00:36:57,160 --> 00:36:59,480
Doctor, tell it to shut up!

524
00:36:59,560 --> 00:37:02,760
-Cleaves, no. No, no.
-Circuit probe.

525
00:37:02,840 --> 00:37:05,840
Fires about, oh, 40,000 volts?
Would kill any one of us.

526
00:37:05,920 --> 00:37:08,800
So I guess she'll work on Gangers
just the same.

527
00:37:08,880 --> 00:37:11,520
It's interesting you refer
to them as "it"

528
00:37:11,600 --> 00:37:14,360
but you call a glorified cattle prod
a "she".

529
00:37:14,440 --> 00:37:16,440
When the real people
are safely off this island

530
00:37:16,520 --> 00:37:19,640
then I'll happily talk philosophy
over a pint with you, Doctor.

531
00:37:19,720 --> 00:37:21,000
What are you going to do to them?

532
00:37:21,080 --> 00:37:24,040
Sorry, they're monsters. Mistakes.

533
00:37:24,120 --> 00:37:27,080
-They have to be destroyed.
-Give me the probe, Cleaves.

534
00:37:27,160 --> 00:37:30,120
We always have to take charge,
don't we, Miranda.

535
00:37:30,200 --> 00:37:32,840
Even when we don't really know
what the hell is going on.

536
00:37:34,600 --> 00:37:35,600
(GRUNTS)

537
00:37:37,960 --> 00:37:40,600
Oh! Agh! Dead!

538
00:37:40,680 --> 00:37:43,320
We call it decommissioned.

539
00:37:43,400 --> 00:37:45,400
-(GASPS)
-You stopped his heart.

540
00:37:45,480 --> 00:37:47,600
He had a heart!

541
00:37:47,680 --> 00:37:52,080
Aorta, valves, a real human heart!

542
00:37:53,200 --> 00:37:55,240
And you stopped it.

543
00:37:55,320 --> 00:37:56,640
-Jen?
-What happened to Buzz

544
00:37:56,720 --> 00:37:58,800
will happen to us all if we trust you!

545
00:37:58,880 --> 00:38:00,720
Wait, wait. Just wait.

546
00:38:01,320 --> 00:38:05,320
-No! (GRUNTS)
-(SCREAMS)

547
00:38:05,480 --> 00:38:08,040
(GRUNTS) Idiot!

548
00:38:08,120 --> 00:38:09,240
Wait!

549
00:38:11,840 --> 00:38:12,840
(CLEAVES PANTING)

550
00:38:16,960 --> 00:38:19,600
Look at what you have done, Cleaves!

551
00:38:19,680 --> 00:38:24,080
If it's war, then it's war.
You don't get it, Doctor.

552
00:38:24,160 --> 00:38:27,400
How can you? It's us and them now.

553
00:38:29,400 --> 00:38:34,080
-Us and them.
-Us and them.

554
00:38:38,400 --> 00:38:41,440
(SIGHS) Us and them.

555
00:38:44,040 --> 00:38:45,120
(SIGHS)

556
00:38:45,200 --> 00:38:49,080
You tried.
We all tried and look what they did.

557
00:38:49,840 --> 00:38:52,600
-Us and them now.
-Us and them.

558
00:38:52,680 --> 00:38:54,080
Us and them.

559
00:38:55,040 --> 00:38:57,040
-Jennifer.
-Buzzer warned you it was a trick

560
00:38:57,120 --> 00:38:58,960
and now he's dead.

561
00:38:59,040 --> 00:39:03,600
If we want to live,
then it's time to go to war.

562
00:39:04,920 --> 00:39:08,120
I'll take care of the spare one
running around out there.

563
00:39:12,920 --> 00:39:13,920
(DOOR CLANGS SHUT)

564
00:39:19,720 --> 00:39:21,240
(WHIMPERING)

565
00:39:30,640 --> 00:39:36,440
Trust me. Ahhh...

566
00:39:37,040 --> 00:39:38,280
Oh!

567
00:39:44,880 --> 00:39:48,200
-I just wanted to help her.
-Well, we all do, okay?

568
00:39:48,280 --> 00:39:51,680
-Don't be like that. Listen, she's...
-I said I agree with you, so drop it.

569
00:39:51,920 --> 00:39:54,080
(ARGUMENT CONTINUES, INDISTINCT)

570
00:39:58,640 --> 00:40:02,360
The most fortified and defendable room
in the monastery.

571
00:40:02,440 --> 00:40:06,280
Cleaves, the most fortified
and defendable room in the monastery?

572
00:40:06,360 --> 00:40:07,400
-The chapel.
-Thank you.

573
00:40:07,480 --> 00:40:10,880
Only one way in,
stone walls two feet thick.

574
00:40:10,960 --> 00:40:12,880
You've crossed one hell of a line,
Cleaves.

575
00:40:12,960 --> 00:40:16,280
You've killed one of them.
They're coming back.

576
00:40:18,640 --> 00:40:20,160
In a big way.

577
00:40:32,520 --> 00:40:34,720
-Jennifer!
-Rory?

578
00:40:51,200 --> 00:40:52,240
What about the flares?

579
00:40:52,320 --> 00:40:54,240
We'll worry about the flares
when we're locked inside.

580
00:40:54,320 --> 00:40:56,040
-(JENNIFER SCREAMING)
-Rory Pond.

581
00:40:57,560 --> 00:40:59,800
-Rory, come on.
-Jen's out there.

582
00:41:00,600 --> 00:41:01,680
She's out there and she's on her own.

583
00:41:01,760 --> 00:41:04,120
Well, if she's got any sense,
then she's hiding. Rory!

584
00:41:04,200 --> 00:41:06,520
-I can't leave her out there!
-Rory!

585
00:41:06,600 --> 00:41:09,440
-I know you understand that.
-Get in here! Get in here!

586
00:41:09,520 --> 00:41:10,800
There they are!

587
00:41:11,480 --> 00:41:13,200
-Amy.
-Ah!

588
00:41:14,520 --> 00:41:15,520
Rory!

589
00:41:16,000 --> 00:41:19,320
Amy, they are not after him,
they're after us.

590
00:41:19,400 --> 00:41:22,000
Why? Why?

591
00:41:23,720 --> 00:41:25,560
Show yourself. Show yourself!

592
00:41:25,640 --> 00:41:26,760
(GRUNTING)

593
00:41:28,640 --> 00:41:29,920
Jennifer.

594
00:41:33,640 --> 00:41:35,720
Doctor, pass me the barrel.

595
00:41:36,480 --> 00:41:39,520
We need something heavy,
anything you can find.

596
00:41:43,280 --> 00:41:47,280
This is insane! (CHUCKLING)
We're fighting ourselves!

597
00:41:47,360 --> 00:41:51,760
Yes, it's insane. And it's about to get
even more insanerer.

598
00:41:51,840 --> 00:41:54,640
-Is that a word?
-Show yourself, right now!

599
00:41:54,720 --> 00:41:57,360
Doctor, we are trapped in here
and Rory's out there with them.

600
00:41:57,440 --> 00:41:59,880
Hello! We can't get to the Tardis
and we can't leave the island.

601
00:41:59,960 --> 00:42:01,880
DOCTOR GANGER: Correct
in every respect, Pond.

602
00:42:01,960 --> 00:42:04,040
It's frightening, unexpected,

603
00:42:04,120 --> 00:42:07,360
frankly a total,
utter, splattering mess on the carpet.

604
00:42:07,440 --> 00:42:11,720
But I am certain, 100% certain,
that we can work this out.

605
00:42:12,440 --> 00:42:13,720
Trust me.

606
00:42:15,520 --> 00:42:17,040
I'm the Doctor.

607
00:42:47,440 --> 00:42:48,840
I have a plan.

608
00:42:48,920 --> 00:42:51,600
Oh! You're hurting me.

609
00:42:51,680 --> 00:42:54,360
And it'll destroy them all.

610
00:42:54,440 --> 00:42:56,320
(GRUNTS) Ah! Why?

611
00:42:56,400 --> 00:42:59,240
You're one of us, Doctor.

612
00:42:59,320 --> 00:43:01,120
Nooo!

613
00:43:06,600 --> 00:43:07,600
Oh!

614
00:43:08,000 --> 00:43:09,080
(SCREAMS)

615
00:43:09,160 --> 00:43:10,160
(GASPS)

616
00:43:13,280 --> 00:43:14,280
(GASPS)

617
00:43:14,600 --> 00:43:15,600
(SCREAMS)

